Package org.spongepowered.api.world.generation

Interface GenerationRegion

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BiomeVolume, BiomeVolume.Mutable<GenerationRegion>, BiomeVolume.Streamable<GenerationRegion>, BlockEntityVolume, BlockEntityVolume.Mutable<GenerationRegion>, BlockEntityVolume.Streamable<GenerationRegion>, BlockVolume, BlockVolume.Mutable<GenerationRegion>, BlockVolume.Streamable<GenerationRegion>, ChunkVolume, EntityVolume, EntityVolume.Mutable<GenerationRegion>, EntityVolume.Streamable<GenerationRegion>, EnvironmentalVolume, GenerationVolume, GenerationVolume.Mutable, HeightAwareVolume, LocationBaseDataHolder, LocationBaseDataHolder.Mutable, MutableGameVolume, MutableVolume, PhysicsAwareMutableBlockVolume<GenerationRegion>, PrimitiveGameVolume, ProtoWorld<GenerationRegion>, RandomProvider, Region<GenerationRegion>, UpdatableVolume, Volume
    public interface GenerationRegion
extends ProtoWorld<GenerationRegion>
    A generating region of PrimitiveChunks that are in the stages of being generated for a World and eventually will become Chunk instances. A region is similar to a World in that there are PrimitiveChunks available, BlockStates are used in this region, and likewise, the region can contain and store BlockEntity instances being generated, Entity instances being generated or spawned by generation, etc. The major difference is that a generation region cannot be utilized for ServerLocations, nor is it considered to be viewable by Players or accessible by the Server or World(s).

      • chunkAtBlock

        default PrimitiveChunk chunkAtBlock​(int x,
                                    int y,
                                    int z)
        Description copied from interface: ChunkVolume
        Gets the loaded chunk at the given chunk coordinate position. The position is the block position relative to the ProtoChunk.chunkPosition(), and therefor is going to return a different chunk from ChunkVolume.chunk(Vector3i). This is more usable from ServerLocations or a Locatable that returns a position in relation to a ProtoWorld.
        Specified by:
        chunkAtBlock in interface ChunkVolume
        Parameters:
        x - The x coordinate
        y - The y coordinate
        z - The z coordinate
        Returns:
        The chunk, if available

      • chunk

        default PrimitiveChunk chunk​(org.spongepowered.math.vector.Vector3i chunkPosition)
        Description copied from interface: ChunkVolume
        Gets the loaded chunk at the given chunk coordinate position. The position is the same as ProtoChunk.chunkPosition(). The difference between a block placed within a ProtoWorld is different from a ProtoChunk's position, and therefore care should be taken when requesting a chunk. It is not guaranteed that the returned ProtoChunk is empty or not, nor the state of the chunk.
        Specified by:
        chunk in interface ChunkVolume
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • chunk

        PrimitiveChunk chunk​(int cx,
                     int cy,
                     int cz)
        Description copied from interface: ChunkVolume
        Gets the loaded chunk at the given chunk coordinate position. The position is the same as ProtoChunk.chunkPosition(). The difference between a block placed within a ProtoWorld is different from a ProtoChunk's position, and therefore care should be taken when requesting a chunk. It is not guaranteed that the returned ProtoChunk is empty or not, nor the state of the chunk.

        In Vanilla, the y coordinate will always be 0.

        Specified by:
        chunk in interface ChunkVolume
        Parameters:
        cx - The x coordinate
        cy - The y coordinate
        cz - The z coordinate
        Returns:
        The chunk, may be empty
